in ufo the player has two hitboxes, one defined by a square defined by two (x,y) pairs, one for the top left corner and bottom right

square bullets have a center (x,y) and a size (w,h)
from that you can get the two corners by subtracting/adding half of the width/height from the center
then you do a standard square-square intersection check to see if the bullet hits you
if it doesn't hit you it does a second check, but with a fake bullet of size 48 instead
if that fake bullet would hit you it is counted as a graze instead
circle hitbox bullets are mostly the same, but the math is wrong because zun failed algebra https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Freshman%27s_dream
p_r**2 + b_r**2 > (p_x - b_x)**2 + (p_y - b_y)**2 means you got hit
the already tiny hitboxes are even smaller than they are supposed to be because of the math errors
grazing is complicated because the math is even more incorrect, but basically it does the same checks but the player's hitbox radius is increased by 40

You were processing these thoughts as you worked in the kitchen while making lunch, lately the wild youkai have been winding down as they've either been exterminated by hunters, Reimu, or turned to other food sources and thus weren't a threat anymore so today Reimu had off.
Like usual the lazy miko took to her veranda to soak up the spring sun and started napping despite the smell of cooking food wafting out from the kitchen. It wasn't long before you were done making the Ikanago, a dish made from small eels that spawned rapidly this seasons in most of the waterways. You were confident she'd love it as you were able to get it fresh this morning and knew it paired well with sake, you were pulling out all the stops after all since more then anything you wanted to see her usual smiling face you've grown accustomed too and got ready the cask of plum wine you've had fermenting. It wasn't long till you plated the food and brought out both of your servings on trays and placed the perpendicular on the table, fondly remembering the days when Reimu would get cozy at your side while eating. after setting the table you approached the sleepy miko, gently shaking her shoulder and whispering, "wake up, its time for lunch dear~" and she roused from her sleep, rubbing her eyes as you admired your lovers' adorable mannerisms. Sadly her features soon turned back to that emotionless facade that pains you more then any wound could as she woke properly and gave a small nod, "right". She got up and and sat at the table as you were moving inside the kitchen to gather the cups to enjoy the plum wine and once you turned back to make to the table you were disappointed to learn that she moved her tray to the opposite side of yours, but that didn't stop your stride. With a prideful voice you announced, "today should be the day when the plum wines' fully ready so I thought we could enjoy it with the eels!" to that Reimu paused for a second and with a voice that hinted more at tiredness then anything else she let out a, "We'll see if you could make it right...". Her reaction wasn't what you were hoping for, two months ago when you started it you knew Reimu couldn't wait to try it, but recently its been tiresome in how much she's been criticizing you for things you know she likes. You'd never voice it though, not only unaware of how things were to become but also because deep down in your soul you felt fear ever since that night, you were unwilling to raise your voice to Reimu again and simply accepted her behavior as the subtle fear warned against angering her again. "I hope it meets your expectations then!" you forced out a cheerful reply as you poured a cup for her from the cask, the fermented plums poured out into the cup along with the sweet liquid into her cup, you knew that liked to nibble on them as she drank but with a reluctant face she accepted the cup and sighed as she took her first sip. "Its not the worst but really you need to learn how do these things properly!" you nodded and agreed generically as you took a sip yourself from your cup, the flavor was flawless and exactly as she liked it but the subtle fear kept you from voicing your opinion.
Reimu drank a cup despite her protests initially, soon another and another as the sour sweetness masked the alcohol and you as you were both finished with the lunch you made to take the dishes to the wash basin and after you made to move the cask of wine to storage as well which Reimu put her hand on it as you did and said in a firm voice, "leave it..." you didn't want to make her mad so you cautiously said, "Dear, plum wine takes a while to make... surely you wouldn't want to waste it all during the middle of the day?". With those words Reimu poured the cup back and devoured the plum in her cup as well before looking you in the eyes and saying slightly more tipsy, "I'll drink what I please dammit! what are you trying to piss me off again?!". You could do nothing but take a seat next to her and sip at your own wine while she got drunk off your labor and patience not wanting to make her more cross, you simply tried keeping the wine offset with snacks as inside you felt nothing but a deep despair...

>What is this?

Era games are a group of (usually) Japanese-developed text porn games.
They're not exclusively related to the Touhou franchise, but it's one of the series with most era games.

>Games usually discussed here
eraTohoTW - Comfy Touhou dating simulator with timestop shenanigans.
eraTohoK - Tactical game about conquering Gensokyo through any (absolutely any) means.
eraMegaten - Dungeon crawler based on the Shin Megami Tensei series, with tons of characters from other series (Fate, Touhou, Madoka, etc) included.

>Links
- WIKI: https://wiki.eragames.rip/index.php/Main_Page
Guides and downloads for all era games. For TW you should get the eng-development version, eng-release is several years old.
- GIT: https://gitgud.io/era-games
Git repository that has latest official builds to any of the games, you can sometimes find more recent versions than the ones on the wiki.
- AUTO UPDATER: http://madhammer.club/files/era-updater.7z
Fetches the latest version of TW, K or Megaten from the official git, no login needed.
- TW NEODEV: https://gitgud.io/Pedy/pedy-tw/-/releases
Git repository with a version of TW that gets more frequent updates. Might introduce more bugs, though they usually get fixed on the following release.
- JAP WIKI: https://seesaawiki.jp/eraseries/
- TRANSLATOR: https://wiki.eragames.rip/index.php/Sugoi
Automatic translator which copies text straight from the game. Comes with an optional customized built-in offline model.
You can also download the latest version at:
https://drive.google.com/file/d/1KgAsQzI-A0D8vmNIekwIRKlflGw9xz3i/view
- BUGS?: https://wiki.eragames.rip/bugreport.php
Report them over here.

>How to play?
Run anchor.exe, japanese locale is advised so you don't run into untranslated text.
If you wish to manually update, delete old files aside the sav and dat folders to avoid any bugs.

>How can I help?
Read https://wiki.eragames.rip/index.php/Contributing for starters.
You could try your hand at translating dialogue, there are guides currently in the TW folder (in #Translation) on what to do, not sure if it that folder exists in other games.
Another guide is:
1) Download an IDE. VS Code, for example.
1a) If using VS Code, install the EraBasic addon
2) Select UTF8 encoding
3) Open the ERB files and edit them
That way you can now edit files without much trouble.
The path for files to edit is usually the ERB folder:
K: ERB/口上
TW: ERB\口上・メッセージ関連\個人口上

You can also report bugs or typos here on the thread when you see them.
If you'd like to either edit or add your own portraits, the files are located within the 'resources' folder in webp format. You can use paint.net to edit them
